-- Itron Meter Contracts to Help Cut India Water Losses
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-06-20T15:46:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-20/itron-smart-meter-contracts-in-india-to-help-reduce-water-losses.html
(Corrects company name in second paragraph)  Itron Inc. (ITRI) , a maker of smart meters
that reduce waste and energy, has been awarded a contract by
Indiaâ€™s biggest engineering company to help curb water losses
and improve infrastructure in the New Delhi area.  Larsen & Toubro Ltd. (LT)  selected Itron to provide 120,000
advanced meters to Delhi Jal Board as part of a project to
measure usage and more effectively deliver water to Delhi
residents, the Liberty Lake, Washington-based company said in a
statement.  Itron also won a contract from  SPML Infra Ltd. (SPML)  to provide
90,000 meters to DJB in the Malviya Nagar, Vasant Vihar and
Mehrauli areas of Delhi. A group led by Suez Environnement and
SPML aim in a pilot program to improve water distribution,
ensure service throughout the day and reduce water losses. No
contract terms were disclosed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
